      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_8bc967591435f71830fe64f455855577">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by Rex Whistler, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0bd140bd81d7047e039127ad368d48b9">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Reginald John Whistler (1905-1944) was an English painter and illustrator. He was born in London and died in action in Normandy during World War II.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d3cd95e75765b48354eb769f9e60c364">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection comprises a small number of bookplates by Rex Whistler as well as a few related materials, including correspondence and ephemera.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_8f0e14198a30a97786da6d756105f32a">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Bookplates. II. Correspondence and Ephemera.</p>  
      </arrangement>
